{"URCEOLAR":[{"def":"Shaped like a pitcher or urn; swelling below, and contrasted at the orifice, as a calyx or corolla.","pos":""}],"URCEOLE":[{"def":"A vessel for water for washing the hands; also, one to hold wine or water.","pos":""}],"URCEOLUS":[{"def":"Any urn-shaped organ of a plant.","pos":""}],"URCHIN":[{"def":"A mischievous elf supposed sometimes to take the form a hedgehog.","pos":""},{"def":"A pert or roguish child; -- now commonly used only of a boy.","pos":""}],"URCHON":[{"def":"The urchin, or hedgehog.","pos":""}]}